# LegacyCraft DevKit - class mappings (SRG format)
# Format: CL: <obfClass> <deobfClass>
#
# Every entry below is grounded in the actual bytecode of b1.7.3 client.jar.
# Names use the Lc prefix throughout. Where bytecode does not unambiguously
# reveal a class's purpose, no entry is written.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Networking
# Evidence: ki is abstract with read(DataInputStream), write(DataOutputStream),
# handle(<handler>), getId() methods, and a static block that registers 57
# subclasses against integer packet ids. ti is the handler interface that
# every packet's a(ti) method dispatches to.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

CL: ki net/legacycraft/network/LcPacket
CL: ti net/legacycraft/network/LcPacketHandler

# Packet body classes - registered in ki's static initializer with explicit
# integer packet ids. Names below preserve the registered id so the binding
# from bytecode to source is one-to-one and verifiable.

CL: lz net/legacycraft/network/packet/LcPacket000
